When he's sure the flame has caught, he turns to his charge and begins stripping him of his sopping, snow-laden clothes. Prince John shudders violently in the growing amber light, and his lack of fight concerns Ghost more than even the blue tinge to his lips. /4
Wet layers fall to the floor, revealing damp, goose-pimpled skin. Ghost carries John to the hearth, laying him as close as he dares to the flames before removing his own wet clothing. /5

"The gift of the elements, remember?"

As he speaks, he ups the temperature of his hands, pressing them into the trembling back of the man he's sworn to protect with his life. He hadn't known the prince then, the vow coerced from him by John's father, the previous king, instead of freely given. /8

But as Ghost came to know the headstrong yet soft-hearted prince, it quickly became the most important of his vows.

That is to say, it became a matter of devotion rather than obligation.

Luckily, John doesn't know that. /9

"So now you've seen me, what do you think? Am I as ugly as you supposed?"

It's a reversal of their running joke, one John has become more pressing about the longer they spend in one another's company. /11

Since the assassination of John's father and the bitter civil war over the line of succession between John and his stepbrother Phillip, Ghost has been John's shadow, trailing after him to every meeting, every hunting party, and every journey outside the castle grounds. /12

The moment is far too intimate for what they are to one another‚Äîjust a soon-to-be monarch and his faithful mage guardian who is more dead than alive. But Ghost revels in the way John's attention is fully focused on him, in the way his fingers skate over the scar that cuts through Ghost's cheek‚Äî /16

In the way their breath mingles as they lean closer.

"Sorry to tell you, Johnny, but you don't scare me," Ghost murmurs.

"N-not even a little?"

"Nope."

"Ye dinnae scare me either, Ghost of the Hill."

The kiss is softer than anything Ghost deserves. /17

John just graces him with a well-pleased smile and lays his head on Ghost's shoulder. His shivering has died down, and when his breathing becomes a soft, even refrain, Ghost slowly lays him down on the blankets and extracts himself to spread their clothes out to dry. /19
